---
const img = '/sharenote-example.png';
---
<section class="note-explainer-section py-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1040px] px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-6">
    <div class="explainer-grid">
      <div class="copy">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl leading-snug font-bold">How does a Sharenote look like?</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] mb-4">A Sharenote is the banknote you print for the Web of Fun: proof of the work you resolved, styled around the work template you picked, and ready to spend on social engagements, resolving coin-mining blocks, buying intelligence, and more.</p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] mb-4">To print one, you need three things:</p>
        <ul class="points">
          <li>Work templates from work providers</li>
          <li>Hardware tuned to the target hash algorithm</li>
          <li>Energy you dedicate to power the print</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="image-col">
        <div class="explainer-wrap">
          <picture>
            <source type="image/avif" srcset="/optimized/sharenote-example-w480.avif 480w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w640.avif 640w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w820.avif 820w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w1024.avif 1024w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 680px, (min-width: 768px) 44vw, 92vw" />
            <source type="image/webp" srcset="/optimized/sharenote-example-w480.webp 480w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w640.webp 640w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w820.webp 820w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w1024.webp 1024w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 680px, (min-width: 768px) 44vw, 92vw" />
            <img src="/sharenote-example.png" srcset="/optimized/sharenote-example-w480.png 480w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w640.png 640w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w820.png 820w, /optimized/sharenote-example-w1024.png 1024w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 680px, (min-width: 768px) 44vw, 92vw" alt="Sharenote example" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="example-img" />
          </picture>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="edge top" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="edge bottom" aria-hidden="true"></div>
</section>

<style>
  .note-explainer-section {
    --prev-bg: #e6c999;
    --note-bg: #edf9c5;
    background: var(--note-bg);
    position: relative; color: var(--ink);
    padding-top: clamp(56px, 10vw, 88px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(56px, 10vw, 88px);
  }
  :global(.dark) .note-explainer-section { --note-bg: color-mix(in oklab, #edf9c5 16%, var(--bg)); }
  /* No full-bleed edges when not full width */
  .note-explainer-section .edge { display: none; }
  .explainer-grid { display: grid; align-items: center; gap: 20px; }
  @media (min-width: 768px) { .explainer-grid { grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr; gap: 32px; } }
  @media (min-width: 1200px) { .explainer-grid { grid-template-columns: 1.6fr 1fr; gap: 40px; } }
  .copy { padding: 8px 0; }
  .copy .points { margin: 0; padding-left: 1rem; }
  .copy .points li { margin: 6px 0; }
  .image-col { display: grid; align-items: center; justify-items: end; }
  .explainer-wrap { position: relative; margin: 0; width: 100%; max-width: 720px; }
  .example-img { display: block; width: 100%; height: auto;  box-shadow: 0 10px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.14), 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); }
</style>
